# MovieList — performance (screens and components)

## When to optimize

- Apply **`React.memo`** to **pure** list items or heavy subtrees that re-render often from parent state.
- Use **`useCallback`** for handlers passed to **memoized** children or **`FlatList`** props like **`renderItem`**, **`keyExtractor`**, **`onEndReached`** when profiling shows churn.
- Use **`useMemo`** for **expensive** derived data or filtered lists — avoid preemptive micro-memoization everywhere.

## Lists

- Stable **`keyExtractor`**. Avoid inline **object/array literals** in **`extraData`** and similar props when they cause needless list rerenders.

## Images

- Prefer TMDB sizes appropriate to layout (centralize in **`image.ts`** / theme). Avoid oversized decode work on tiny thumbnails.
